                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4001/13.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Snyder</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Holland Bay, Jamaica</hi>
                        </placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 22, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Estimate 1,500 instantly killed; about 900 buried; others burned where found;
                    many injured dead since; after inquiry learn no Americans identified dead or
                    injured. Kingston Hotel not yet cleared; Americans presumed buried there.
                    Approximate total deaths 1,800. No scarcity food. Medicines, disinfectants
                    urgently needed. Water supply fair. Thirty thousand reported homeless. Clearing
                    streets of debris rapidly pursued. People tranquil.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Snyder.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
